description.narrative: The polio free status was sustained during 2019 in Syria with four national and sub-national immunization days that reached 2.4 million girls and boys under the age of five (around 50% girls), and the routine immunization programme revitalization has continued with 357,877 girls and boys under the age of one year (around 50% girls) vaccinated with Penta 3 as of November 2019 compared with 318,518 vaccinated during the same period in 2018. These gains are especially more remarkable in the least performing governorate of 2018, with 24,540 children reached in 2019 in Deir-ez-Zor compared to 3,234 in 2018. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:19/01/2020
